21:38.338 --> 21:39.338
Will do.

21:51.518 --> 21:55.022
Hey, Carmen, Detective Duvall.
Is conference room three available?

21:55.814 --> 21:57.254
Great, will you block it off for me?

21:57.316 --> 22:00.235
The sexual assault at the Blackhill
that came in at midday.

22:00.694 --> 22:01.694
Thank you.

22:03.155 --> 22:04.155
She'd like to see you.

22:16.585 --> 22:17.586
Hi, Amber.

22:19.838 --> 22:20.881
How you doin'?

22:21.757 --> 22:22.757
I'm okay.

22:23.216 --> 22:24.216
Good.

22:25.177 --> 22:26.386
Did they find anything?

22:27.137 --> 22:29.848
The cops? Any evidence or whatever?

22:30.265 --> 22:32.142
A few things, it's...

22:32.976 --> 22:36.188
it's too early to say if any of it
is related to the assailant,

22:36.438 --> 22:38.774
but all of it will be thoroughly examined.

22:41.735 --> 22:42.735
Okay.

22:46.073 --> 22:48.533
He seemed like he really knew
what he was doing, you know?

22:50.202 --> 22:51.495
He was really careful.

22:52.871 --> 22:57.292
Okay, Amber, I've got some medications
here for you and some paperwork.

22:57.376 --> 22:59.086
We can go through it now if you like.

22:59.169 --> 23:02.047
But if you'd prefer to keep resting
for a bit, that's fine too.

23:02.130 --> 23:04.216
You can do it later. Entirely up to you.

23:12.099 --> 23:13.683
Do you know where you wanna go?

23:13.767 --> 23:15.394
Um...

23:16.353 --> 23:17.687
not home.

23:17.771 --> 23:18.771
Okay.

23:19.481 --> 23:21.358
Is there a friend you can stay with?

23:21.691 --> 23:23.318
Yeah. Um...

23:23.402 --> 23:24.986
Yeah, I just, I gotta call her.

23:29.741 --> 23:31.618
Sorry. Thank you.

23:53.098 --> 23:54.307
Yeah. Um...

23:55.183 --> 23:56.183
I...

23:58.270 --> 23:59.270
Oh.

24:00.313 --> 24:01.940
I, uh...

24:02.023 --> 24:03.483
I can't go home.

24:04.985 --> 24:06.236
Can I, um...

24:07.154 --> 24:09.906
Can I... can I come to you?

24:11.366 --> 24:12.742
Can I come stay with you?

24:24.629 --> 24:25.839
Is that your family?

24:27.007 --> 24:28.007
Yeah.

24:29.843 --> 24:30.843
Cute girls.

24:31.553 --> 24:32.553
Thanks.

24:36.892 --> 24:38.185
What's that?

24:41.563 --> 24:42.563
Uh...

24:43.482 --> 24:45.150
that's just a little reminder.

24:45.442 --> 24:47.569
- Of what?
- What I'm doing, I guess.

24:48.278 --> 24:49.529
It's from Isaiah.

24:51.281 --> 24:52.532
God shows up...

24:54.159 --> 24:56.161
looking for someone to be of service.

24:58.205 --> 24:59.498
Clean things up a bit.

25:00.832 --> 25:03.126
He says, "Whom shall I send?"

25:19.142 --> 25:20.810
So, this is my cell.

25:21.728 --> 25:23.355
Just call anytime.

25:23.730 --> 25:24.730
Okay.

25:30.695 --> 25:32.364
Okay, I'm making dinner,

25:32.447 --> 25:36.034
and there's a hot bath waiting for you,
and a cup of tea and some wine.

25:36.535 --> 25:37.775
I didn't know which you'd want.

25:38.703 --> 25:40.455
Thank you for taking care of her.

25:42.832 --> 25:45.043
Get some rest. I'll be in touch.

25:55.804 --> 25:57.973
Three suspicious males mentioned
by the neighbors.

25:58.056 --> 25:59.099
We tracked down one.

25:59.182 --> 26:02.644
He was at work all morning.
Confirmed by coworkers, boss, and video.

26:03.186 --> 26:06.231
Another was in a Winnebago parked
in front of the complex for a few days.

26:06.648 --> 26:09.484
It had moved on by the time
of the assault, but we're following up.

26:09.568 --> 26:12.654
And the third is a resident of the complex
who wasn't home when we knocked.

26:12.737 --> 26:14.017
This will all be in the reports.

26:15.407 --> 26:17.617
- Which I'll get by...
- It'll be ready by the morning.

26:17.701 --> 26:20.054
- I got my guys working on 'em now.
- Tell 'em to be thorough.

26:20.078 --> 26:23.456
If I get one like that piece of garbage
Inky filed on the B and E...

26:23.540 --> 26:25.750
- I'll make sure.
- You saw that thing, right?

26:26.042 --> 26:28.712
It's practically scrawled
on a cocktail napkin.

26:29.087 --> 26:31.089
He's aware. It won't happen again.

26:32.757 --> 26:33.757
Good.

26:34.342 --> 26:35.802
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

26:45.312 --> 26:47.731
I don't know if he made a noise,

26:47.814 --> 26:50.358
or if I just sensed him there,
but all of a sudden,

26:50.442 --> 26:51.711
<i>I was wide-awake.</i>

26:51.735 --> 26:53.087
<i>Do you know
what kind of gun it was?</i>

26:53.111 --> 26:54.404
<i>I don't know about guns.</i>

26:54.571 --> 26:56.114
If you scream, I'll kill you.

26:56.489 --> 26:57.407
<i>I have money.</i>

26:57.490 --> 27:00.327
Fuck you. Take those off.

27:01.745 --> 27:03.788
- <i>Then he dressed me up.
- How?</i>

27:06.416 --> 27:08.335
He wanted me to look like a hooker.

27:08.960 --> 27:10.337
And like a little girl.

27:11.129 --> 27:12.881
- <i>Both.</i>
- Lie down.

27:18.678 --> 27:19.846
Here you go, Detective.

27:37.614 --> 27:38.614
Then he started.

27:40.700 --> 27:42.118
And then he would just stop.

27:42.535 --> 27:44.120
He did that eight times.

27:44.829 --> 27:46.831
Stopped and then started again.

27:47.248 --> 27:49.935
- <i>And each time he just sat there?
- Or took pictures.</i>

27:49.959 --> 27:51.959
<i>He was white.</i>

27:52.087 --> 27:54.839
Around six-two, 170, 180 maybe.

27:55.090 --> 27:57.175
- So fairly lean.
- Yeah.

27:57.467 --> 28:00.220
<i>But with a belly,
like he wasn't in shape.</i>

28:01.888 --> 28:05.684
<i>He was wearing black sneakers,
gray sweatpants with holes in the knees.</i>

28:05.767 --> 28:09.979
<i>He had blond hair on his arms and legs,
but his pubic hair was shaved.</i>

28:11.898 --> 28:13.608
<i>And he has a birthmark. A big one.</i>

28:14.734 --> 28:15.734
Where?

28:18.154 --> 28:19.197
His left calf?

28:19.531 --> 28:22.534
Or looking at him, was it on your left?

28:22.826 --> 28:23.826
His left.

28:25.370 --> 28:26.454
You sure about that?

28:26.746 --> 28:27.746
Yes.

28:43.638 --> 28:45.432
Marie. Got a minute?

28:47.267 --> 28:48.267
Yeah.

28:53.189 --> 28:54.649
How you doing, Marie?

28:56.484 --> 28:58.778
- I'm okay.
- Work's okay? Classes okay?

28:59.738 --> 29:01.531
Yeah, work's good. Yeah.

29:01.614 --> 29:05.368
I didn't get to make it
to that photography class.

29:05.452 --> 29:06.828
I was just, um...

29:08.371 --> 29:10.665
But I... I'll... I'll just go next week

29:10.749 --> 29:13.251
and email the teacher
to find out what I missed.

29:13.334 --> 29:14.711
Okay, sounds good.

29:15.587 --> 29:16.588
So, listen.

29:17.255 --> 29:19.340
I hope you know by now
how much we love you here.

29:19.424 --> 29:21.176
Yeah. We think you're awesome.

29:21.509 --> 29:23.762
And we're serious about the commitment
we made to you.

29:23.845 --> 29:25.805
To this whole transition
out of foster care.

29:25.889 --> 29:27.849
It's hard.
Nobody expects it to be seamless.

29:27.932 --> 29:29.492
Lots of our kids hit bumps in the road.

29:29.517 --> 29:31.227
- Most of them.
- Most of them, yeah.

29:31.811 --> 29:34.397
And this whole thing
definitely qualifies as a bump.

29:34.689 --> 29:35.689
Right?

29:37.609 --> 29:39.194
But that's what we're here for.

29:39.611 --> 29:40.611
The thing is,

29:41.029 --> 29:43.364
we also have an obligation
to this community.

29:43.740 --> 29:47.869
To the agreements that hold it together.
And the most important of those is that

29:48.161 --> 29:49.746
we be straight with each other.

29:50.121 --> 29:52.791
Can't have community without trust, right?

29:54.626 --> 29:56.503
So, not surprisingly,

29:57.045 --> 29:59.506
this whole thing has shaken
people's trust in you.

29:59.839 --> 30:01.549
So we need to address that.

30:01.633 --> 30:03.843
Make some changes to restore that trust.

30:04.552 --> 30:06.054
Wh... what kind of changes?

30:06.137 --> 30:07.948
We're gonna cut back on some
of your freedoms.

30:07.972 --> 30:11.351
Knock your curfew back an hour.
Not forever, but for the time being.

30:11.434 --> 30:13.812
And we're going to do mandatory
daily check-ins.

30:14.479 --> 30:15.313
Why?

30:15.396 --> 30:18.858
I think better communication
will help you to stay on track.

30:18.942 --> 30:20.735
And it'll help us get in there early

30:20.819 --> 30:23.238
and help you process things
before they get out of hand.

30:23.321 --> 30:25.365
- So nothing like this happens again.
- It won't.

30:25.448 --> 30:27.575
We just want to have a mechanism in place.

30:27.659 --> 30:29.661
Well, why? It... it... it's...

30:30.453 --> 30:32.580
It's stupid. Why would I do that again?

30:33.623 --> 30:36.209
It's not like it did me any good.
I mean, everyone hates me.

30:36.292 --> 30:39.504
- I can't even leave my apartment.
- It's important for other kids to see

30:39.587 --> 30:41.881
there are consequences to your actions.

30:43.132 --> 30:45.468
Oh, so this is about them.
It has nothing to do with me.

30:45.552 --> 30:46.553
It's for all of us.

30:48.304 --> 30:50.640
- That's bullshit.
- Nine o'clock curfew.

30:51.015 --> 30:53.935
Nightly 8:45 check-in
with whoever's on duty.

31:37.562 --> 31:38.646
Hey, sweetheart.

31:40.356 --> 31:41.190
Hi.

31:41.274 --> 31:43.460
When I heard the noise,
I thought you were the raccoons.

31:43.484 --> 31:46.946
- Oh, no, it's... it's just me.
- Hey, hey. Come here. Come here.

31:51.242 --> 31:52.368
How you doing, kiddo?

31:54.913 --> 31:56.414
I'm so sorry, honey. God.

31:58.124 --> 31:59.124
Um...

31:59.208 --> 32:03.129
I thought maybe if I could watch
<i>The Bachelor </i> with Colleen, it would, um...

32:04.422 --> 32:07.008
- I don't know, it would, you know...
- Take your mind off stuff.

32:07.091 --> 32:08.635
- Yeah. Yeah.
- I guess, yeah.

32:08.718 --> 32:12.764
It's a good idea, but she's not here.
She's out at a neighborhood meeting.

32:12.847 --> 32:16.434
Um... Okay. Well, maybe I could
just, uh, wait for her.

32:16.809 --> 32:19.187
Uh, I think she's gonna be out late, hon.

32:19.270 --> 32:21.689
I mean, their agenda was, like,
a mile and a half long.

32:21.773 --> 32:23.650
Okay? Well, then I can just, um...

32:24.359 --> 32:27.028
I can watch it by myself.

32:27.946 --> 32:30.448
I don't think that's gonna work either.
Um...

32:32.325 --> 32:35.036
Marie, hon.

32:36.204 --> 32:37.455
You know, I love you.

32:38.665 --> 32:41.501
It's just that right now,
on the heels of all this stuff,

32:41.584 --> 32:42.961
it's probably better...

32:44.504 --> 32:48.633
for you and me not to spend time together
when Colleen's not around too.

32:50.635 --> 32:51.635
Why?

32:51.719 --> 32:53.513
We're foster parents, Marie.

32:53.972 --> 32:56.474
We can't have the slightest blot
on our record.

32:56.557 --> 32:58.476
Okay, so I... I'm... I'm a blot?

32:58.768 --> 33:01.688
No, honey. God, no, you're wonderful.

33:01.771 --> 33:04.357
You know I think the world of you.

33:05.191 --> 33:06.401
Look, it...

33:10.655 --> 33:12.281
I'm not a psychiatrist.

33:13.241 --> 33:16.661
I don't know what made you say that thing
about being attacked.

33:16.744 --> 33:17.787
And I'm not judging.

33:18.454 --> 33:21.249
After all you've been through
and all you've overcome,

33:21.332 --> 33:25.545
hey, even the strongest, best-adjusted kid
is gonna come out of that with some

33:25.878 --> 33:28.715
complicated stuff. And again, no judgment.

33:29.173 --> 33:30.173
I get it.

33:30.466 --> 33:31.466
It's just that...

33:32.343 --> 33:36.222
If you were to ever say anything
like that about me...

33:38.474 --> 33:39.851
It's not personal.

33:39.934 --> 33:42.145
Marie, please, you gotta understand that.

33:43.146 --> 33:45.148
I just have to think of myself

33:45.231 --> 33:49.068
and of all the kids
we want to be able to help here.

33:49.152 --> 33:51.237
Like you were once. Yeah?

33:51.571 --> 33:55.408
Honey, when Colleen's around,
you're more than welcome, anytime.

33:55.491 --> 33:57.535
Hey, ev... even later tonight would work.

33:57.952 --> 33:59.245
- Yeah?
- Uh...

33:59.328 --> 34:01.164
I'll tell her
to call you when she gets home.

34:01.247 --> 34:02.433
That's good. I'm okay.

34:02.457 --> 34:05.137
- I'm sure she won't mind coming to pick...
- I'm all right.

35:09.732 --> 35:10.732
Hello.

35:11.192 --> 35:13.736
I'm Detective Duvall
with the Golden Police Department,

35:13.820 --> 35:17.156
investigating an assault that happened
in this complex this morning.

35:17.240 --> 35:19.117
Do you have a couple minutes to talk?

35:22.203 --> 35:23.454
Mom!

35:24.205 --> 35:27.542
I heard about it from my neighbor Jenny
when we got back this afternoon.

35:27.625 --> 35:29.210
I just... I can't...

35:29.919 --> 35:31.462
When you got back from where?

35:31.546 --> 35:33.756
A camping trip with some friends.

35:33.840 --> 35:34.924
We do it every year.

35:35.007 --> 35:37.635
- How long were you gone?
- Just four days. A long weekend.

35:37.885 --> 35:40.012
- We? That's you and...
- Me and Rowey.

35:40.096 --> 35:42.098
Yeah, it's just us two here.

35:42.807 --> 35:44.433
One small, happy family.

35:44.725 --> 35:47.687
Was it a self-guided trip,
or... or did you use an outfitter?

35:47.770 --> 35:48.855
Oh, self-guided.

35:48.938 --> 35:50.982
Those outfitters,
they'll cost an arm and a leg.

35:51.065 --> 35:52.692
Yeah, no kidding.

35:53.860 --> 35:56.445
So your friends can confirm
you were both there?

35:59.448 --> 36:00.825
Why would they need to do that?

36:05.329 --> 36:07.540
- Did someone accuse Rowey of this?
- No.

36:08.332 --> 36:11.961
- No one has accused him of anything.
- But someone mentioned him.

36:13.629 --> 36:16.757
Mrs. Wilson,
when something like this happens

36:17.175 --> 36:19.635
and people feel suddenly unsafe...

36:19.719 --> 36:22.513
- My son's not a rapist, Detective.
- Did not say he was.

36:34.984 --> 36:35.984
You know,

36:37.153 --> 36:40.573
if one person in this complex
had taken the time to get to know him,

36:40.656 --> 36:42.867
- it really doesn't take much.
- Mrs. Wilson...

36:44.827 --> 36:46.746
I've known a lot of men, Detective,

36:46.829 --> 36:48.748
and it's never the oddballs, okay?

36:49.332 --> 36:50.791
It's the guys that look nice.

36:51.709 --> 36:54.253
The ones that offer to carry
your groceries and buy you a drink.

36:54.921 --> 36:57.256
Those are the ones that turn around
and mess you up.

37:00.092 --> 37:01.719
That's who we were camping with.

37:02.637 --> 37:04.639
Unless you have any other questions...

37:21.614 --> 37:22.615
Hey.

37:22.949 --> 37:23.949
Hey.

37:28.120 --> 37:29.120
Oh, sorry.

37:29.205 --> 37:30.957
It's, uh, it's okay.

37:32.375 --> 37:33.375
They were hungry.

37:34.794 --> 37:36.003
Did she eat?

37:36.754 --> 37:37.754
A little.

37:38.005 --> 37:39.757
<i>♪...My one desire ♪</i>

37:42.134 --> 37:46.055
<i>♪ You got my love
Growing higher and higher ♪</i>

37:48.724 --> 37:49.767
<i>♪ You had... ♪</i>

37:58.401 --> 37:59.777
I just took it.

38:00.569 --> 38:01.612
Ninety-four.

38:02.363 --> 38:05.324
- Hey, that's not bad.
- No, I think we're good.

38:31.225 --> 38:32.225
This is good.

38:32.643 --> 38:33.643
Thank you.

38:34.353 --> 38:35.563
I didn't make it.

38:39.734 --> 38:40.818
She did not.

38:41.694 --> 38:43.362
She did say it was for all of us.

38:43.988 --> 38:45.406
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

38:45.489 --> 38:47.158
You and your inconvenient family?

38:48.075 --> 38:50.244
We're moments away from her
showing up here

38:50.328 --> 38:52.747
in a bikini, saying she locked herself out
of her house

38:52.830 --> 38:56.000
and can you please come help her,
you big, strong police officer?

38:59.128 --> 39:00.128
She's lonely.

39:01.172 --> 39:02.465
Everyone's lonely.

39:07.678 --> 39:08.721
A new case?

39:12.600 --> 39:13.934
You wanna talk about it?

39:18.814 --> 39:19.899
I fixed that drip.

39:20.691 --> 39:21.691
Oh, shoot.

39:22.151 --> 39:24.445
- I was gonna do that.
- I did a half-ass job.

39:25.404 --> 39:27.004
It'll need to be redone in, like, a day.

39:37.166 --> 39:38.292
It's a rape.

39:42.338 --> 39:43.338
Hmm.

39:43.881 --> 39:44.881
Yeah.

39:46.884 --> 39:47.884
Hmm.

39:52.306 --> 39:55.267
Then when he's finally satisfied
with her scrubbing,

39:55.559 --> 39:56.894
he lets her out of the shower

39:56.977 --> 39:59.188
but tells her to stay in the bathroom
until he leaves.

39:59.271 --> 40:00.271
Which she does.

40:00.314 --> 40:03.234
When she hears the door click,
she comes out, he's gone.

40:03.818 --> 40:05.361
So was almost everything he touched.

40:05.611 --> 40:07.947
Her bed sheets, her pillow covers...

40:08.364 --> 40:12.410
I sent a couple things out to the lab,
but from the scene itself, nothing.

40:12.701 --> 40:14.829
Not a hair. Not a fluid.

40:14.912 --> 40:16.872
Nothing. Clean.

40:23.671 --> 40:24.755
He felt smart.

40:27.007 --> 40:28.551
Yeah, but you're smarter.

40:50.948 --> 40:52.992
He took pictures.

40:53.242 --> 40:54.243
The whole time.

40:55.035 --> 40:56.787
Horrible pictures of her

40:57.538 --> 40:59.039
tied up, splayed out.

40:59.874 --> 41:02.874
Said if she told anyone, he'd post them
online with her name and everything.

41:04.378 --> 41:05.880
She called us anyway.

41:07.006 --> 41:08.424
And I asked her why.

41:08.507 --> 41:10.968
She said 'cause she knows
he's gonna do it again

41:11.552 --> 41:12.803
to some other girl.

41:13.554 --> 41:14.739
And she couldn't live with herself

41:14.763 --> 41:17.391
if she didn't at least try
to keep that from happening.

41:25.232 --> 41:26.901
She is one brave young woman.

41:28.736 --> 41:29.987
Did he have a backpack?

41:30.321 --> 41:31.155
What?

41:31.238 --> 41:32.531
The guy. When he did it.

41:33.449 --> 41:34.575
Was he wearing a backpack?

41:35.451 --> 41:37.536
- Yeah. Why?
- We had one like that.

41:38.746 --> 41:41.207
- You should call our detective.
- Who is it?

41:44.502 --> 41:46.337
<i>♪ Girl, it just ain't right ♪</i>

41:48.255 --> 41:49.965
<i>♪ Don't be shy now ♪</i>

41:51.133 --> 41:53.219
<i>♪ 'Cause we're all alone ♪</i>

41:54.553 --> 41:56.430
<i>♪ Let me give you something ♪</i>

41:57.848 --> 41:59.934
<i>♪ That'll shake your bones ♪</i>

42:48.107 --> 42:49.827
Holy, what the...

42:50.359 --> 42:53.654
- Oops, did I scare you?
- Jesus. Fuck! Would...

42:53.737 --> 42:56.699
- Would you get that thing out of my face?
- Oh, sorry about that.

42:58.909 --> 42:59.743
What the fuck?

42:59.827 --> 43:03.038
You know what's funny? I was just asking
myself the same question. What the fuck?

43:03.122 --> 43:06.792
What the fuck is a grown man doing
crawling through the woods,

43:06.875 --> 43:09.712
dressed head to toe like a goddamn
SWAT team member,

43:09.795 --> 43:11.589
in the middle of the night,
behind a building

43:11.672 --> 43:13.215
where a woman was raped last month?

43:13.299 --> 43:15.634
What? I have no idea
what you're talking about.

43:16.468 --> 43:17.720
Who the fuck are you anyway?

43:17.803 --> 43:20.139
Grace Rasmussen, detective,
Westminster PD.

43:20.389 --> 43:23.434
More importantly, friend,
who the fuck are you?

43:24.305 --> 43:30.385
Learn the unknown English words
of this movie at www.skeebdo.com
